UNDIAGNOSED PNEUMONIA - ARGENTINA: (TUCUMÁN) FATAL, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
****************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 31 Aug 2022
Source: National Administration of Laboratories and Health Institutes (ANLIS) [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://msptucuman.gov.ar/analizan-las-muestras-de-los-casos-de-neumonia-de-causa-desconocida-en-tucuman/


The National Administration of Laboratories and Health Institutes (ANLIS) "Dr. Carlos Malbrán" received samples from Tucumán to carry out a diagnostic extension of the 6 cases of pneumonia of unknown origin.

The registered cases correspond to 5 health workers and a patient from a private sanatorium who started having symptoms between [18 and 22 Aug 2022].

In addition, the health authorities are working to carry out the investigation of the outbreak, which includes follow-up of the contacts of the cases and specific control actions in the health center where the outbreak arose.

The registered cases correspond to 5 health workers and a patient from the intensive care unit of a private sanatorium in San Miguel de Tucumán who started having symptoms between [18 and 22 Aug 2022]. The 6 cases presented bilateral pneumonia, 2 of them died, 3 are hospitalized and the remaining 1 is in good health in home isolation. Since [22 Aug 2022], no new cases have been detected.

--
Communicated by:
Andrea Thomas
